09_wave_amp


  1. Question

    A sinusoidal wave is graphed below.


    Estimate the amplitude of the sinusoidal function graphed above.


    Solution

    The amplitude of a sinusoidal function is half the difference between the maximum \(y\) and the minimum \(y\).


    \[A~=~\frac{(0.3)-(-3.5)}{2} ~=~ \frac{3.8}{2} ~=~ 1.9\]

    The amplitude is 1.9.

    This exact function could be plotted with the following algebraic definition: \[y(t) = 1.9 \sin\left(\frac{2\pi}{7.6}(t+7.5)\right)+(-1.6)\]

    The amplitude is 1.9; the period is 7.6; the horizontal shift is left by 7.5; and the midline is \(y=-1.6\).
